[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide has passed 4 million and is 4 059 803, with reports of cases by 216 countries and territories worldwide. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside China now represents 97.9% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA, with more than 1.32 million confirmed cases, now represents 32.7% of the global cases of COVID-19. A global total of 277 988 deaths have been reported, with 273 355 (98.3%) outside mainland China.

In descending rank order, the USA is number 1 for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19, Spain is number 2, and Italy is number 3, followed by the UK, Russia, Germany, France, Brazil, Turkey, and Iran as number 10. China is now number 11. Germany has now moved up from 7th to 6th place and Brazil from 9th to 8th place in terms of cumulative case numbers. Russia reported the highest number of newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (10 817), followed by the USA (6134), with UK reporting the 3rd-highest 24-hour newly confirmed cases (3896). - Mod.UBA]

